Includes two subclasses of inhibitor-resistant TEM (IRT) and complex mutant TEM (CMT) β-lactamases. The IRTs were originally named TRC (TEM enzymes resistant to clavulanic acid), and later TRI (TEM resistant to β-lactamase inhibitors). For a review on IRTs and CMTs see Cantón et al., Clin.
